  "text": "and may assume that δC 3 is decomposed on the basic covariant 3-forms, as in Eq. [CITATION_1] . Clearly, the gauge transformations δC 3 = dα 2 with α 2 = 1 2 E B ∧ E A α AB do not change the field strength and thus are not of any interest at the present stage. If interested in δC 3 variations which produce δH 4 in (34), we can simplify the general expression for δC 3 variation in (35) by factoring out the gauge transformations. Particularly, we can start with δC 3 of the form (17) with",
