  "bib_entries": {
    "121381329": {
      "title": "World volume supersymmetry from space-time supersymmetry of the four-dimensional supermembrane",
      "abstract": "Abstract The d = 4 spacetime, supersymmetric, supermembrane action is the effective action for domain walls in supersymmetric field theories. It is shown to reduce, in a “physical gauge”, to a N = 2 supersymmetric extension of the three-dimensional Volkov-Akulov action, which exhibits a “partial breaking of global supersymmetry” to N = 1. A similar result holds for the d = 2 superparticle for which the world-line superspace form of the gauge-fixed action is found. A consequence of the unbroken N = 1 world-volume supersymmetry is the vanishing of the quantum correction to the classical energy of static membrane configurations."
    }
  }
